  <div class="gameHeader">
    <p>Valorant</p>
  </div>
    
  <div style="clear: both">
    <div class="pSubpage">
          <p class="pItem" style="text-align: center">Valorant is a first-person shooter created by Riot Games. <br>
            It is commonly described as a mix of Counter Strike: Global Offensive or CS:GO and Overwatch.<br>
      Prior to creating Valorant, Riot Games are most known for creating the MOBA game League of Legends.<br>
            Valorant was fully released on June 2, 2020 and it is currently only supported on Windows computers.</p>
          <p class="pItem" style="text-align: center">Valorant has multiple game modes. These game modes are unrated, competitive (also known as ranked),<br> spike rush, deathmatch, escalation, replication, snowball fight and custom game.<br>
            The main game modes are unrated and competitive.<br>
            There are many ranked divisions in Valorant. These ranked divisions in order are <br> iron, bronze, silver, gold, platinum, diamond, ascendant, immortal and radiant.<br>
            All of these ranked divisions are divided into 3 tiers aside from radiant,<br> which only includes the top 500 people from each region at one given time.</p>
    </div>
